OL,3,CAbortion clinic buffer zones to come
OL,4,Cinto effect next month
OL,6,FAnti-abortion groups argued that
OL,7,Fbanning silent prayer would threaten
OL,8,Ftheir rights to freedom of expression
OL,9,Fand religious belief.
OL,11,FSilent prayer is the act of praying
OL,12,Fwithout saying any words. However,
OL,13,Fwhen done outside of a clinic,
OL,14,Fpatients could possibly view it as
OL,15,Fintimidating or uncomfortable.
OL,17,FIt is understood silent prayer could
OL,18,Fcome within the scope of the new law,
OL,19,Fand therefore be a criminal offence if
OL,20,Fdone within the safe access zones.
